ğŸ§¾ Chemical Datasheet â€“ Potassium Permanganate
Chemical Name: Potassium Permanganate
Formula / Structural Diagram: KMnOâ‚„ (ionic compound: Kâº + MnOâ‚„â»)
CAS #: 7722-64-7
Molecular Weight: 158.04 g/mol
Density: 2.70 g/cmÂ³ (at 20 Â°C)
Appearance: Dark purple to almost black crystalline solid, metallic luster, water solutions are
deep purple
âš ï¸ Hazard Information
â— GHS Pictograms: ğŸ”¥â­• (Oxidizer), âš ï¸ (Exclamation mark), â˜£ï¸ (Health hazard), â˜ ï¸
(Acute toxicity)
â— NFPA 704 Diamond:
â—‹ Health: 2
â—‹ Flammability: 0
â—‹ Reactivity: 1
â—‹ Special: OX (oxidizer)
â— Hazard Statements (H-codes):
â—‹ H272: May intensify fire; oxidizer.
â—‹ H302: Harmful if swallowed.
â—‹ H314: Causes severe skin burns and eye damage.
â—‹ H410: Very toxic to aquatic life with long lasting effects.
â— Precautionary Statements (P-codes):
â—‹ P220: Keep/Store away from combustible materials.
â—‹ P260: Do not breathe dust/fumes.
18
â—‹ P280: Wear protective gloves/eye protection/face protection.
â—‹ P305+P351+P338: IF IN EYES: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes.
â—‹ P301+P330+P331: IF SWALLOWED: Rinse mouth. Do NOT induce vomiting.
ğŸ§ª Properties
â— Melting Point: 240 Â°C (decomposes explosively above 240 Â°C)
â— Boiling Point: Decomposes before boiling
â— Solubility: 6.4 g/100 mL water (20 Â°C), freely soluble in water with deep purple solution,
insoluble in ethanol
â— Vapor Pressure: Negligible
â— Other Notes: Strong oxidizer and disinfectant; used in water treatment, analytical
chemistry, and as an antiseptic. Decomposes to MnOâ‚‚ and Oâ‚‚ when heated.
âš ï¸ Handling & Storage
â— Storage Class: Oxidizers (Class 5.1)
â— Conditions: Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated area, away from organic or easily
oxidizable substances. Protect from heat and light.
â— Container Type: Glass or plastic containers resistant to oxidizers.
â— Compatible With: Most inorganic salts.
â— Incompatible With: Acids, alcohols, glycerol, sulfur, peroxides, powdered metals, strong
reducing agents, organic matter.
19
ğŸš¨ Safety Notes
â— First Aid:
â—‹ Skin: Immediately wash with plenty of water for 15 minutes; may cause burns
and brown stains.
â—‹ Eye: Rinse with water for several minutes; seek immediate medical attention.
â—‹ Inhalation: Move to fresh air; seek medical attention if irritation persists.
â—‹ Ingestion: Rinse mouth, do not induce vomiting, seek immediate medical help.
â— Firefighting: Not combustible but accelerates burning; use water spray in large
amounts. Avoid dry chemicals or foam.
â— Spill/Leak Cleanup: Avoid raising dust. Sweep up carefully, collect in a clean dry
container. Wash contaminated areas with large amounts of water.
ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ”¬ Lab Use Notes
â— PPE: Chemical-resistant gloves, safety goggles, lab coat, face shield, dust
mask/respirator if airborne particles.
â— Handling: Handle with extreme care; avoid contact with organics or reducing agents.
Use only with clean equipment.
â— Decomposition Products: Oxygen, manganese dioxide (MnOâ‚‚), and potassium oxide.
â— Disposal: Treat as hazardous oxidizing waste. Dispose of according to local
environmental regulations. Neutralization with reducing agents (like sodium thiosulfate)
before disposal may be required.
