ğŸ§¾ Chemical Datasheet â€“ Barium Chlorate
Chemical Name: Barium Chlorate
Formula / Structural Diagram: Ba(ClOâ‚ƒ)â‚‚
CAS #: 13477-00-4
Molecular Weight: 304.23 g/mol
Density: ~2.74 g/cmÂ³
Appearance: White crystalline solid
âš ï¸ Hazard Information
â— GHS Pictograms: â˜ ï¸ (Toxic), ğŸ”¥â­• (Oxidizer), âš ï¸ (Exclamation mark), ğŸŒŠ
(Environmental hazard)
â— NFPA 704 Diamond:
â—‹ Health: 3
â—‹ Flammability: 0
â—‹ Reactivity: 2
â—‹ Special: OX (oxidizer)
â— Hazard Statements (H-codes):
â—‹ H272: May intensify fire; oxidizer.
â—‹ H301: Toxic if swallowed.
â—‹ H373: May cause damage to organs through prolonged or repeated exposure.
â—‹ H410: Very toxic to aquatic life with long lasting effects.
â— Precautionary Statements (P-codes):
â—‹ P220: Keep/Store away from combustible materials.
â—‹ P260: Do not breathe dust.
â—‹ P270: Do not eat, drink or smoke when using this product.
21
â—‹ P280: Wear protective gloves/eye protection.
â—‹ P301+P310: IF SWALLOWED: Immediately call a POISON CENTER/doctor.
ğŸ§ª Properties
â— Melting Point: ~414 Â°C (decomposes)
â— Boiling Point: Decomposes on heating, does not boil
â— Solubility: 27.5 g/100 mL water (20 Â°C), insoluble in alcohol
â— Vapor Pressure: Negligible
â— Other Notes: Powerful oxidizer, used in pyrotechnics (green flame color due to barium).
Dangerous because of high toxicity from soluble barium salts.
âš ï¸ Handling & Storage
â— Storage Class: Oxidizers (Class 5.1)
â— Conditions: Store in a cool, dry, well-ventilated place. Keep away from heat, organic
materials, and reducing agents.
â— Container Type: Glass or compatible plastic container.
â— Compatible With: Most stable inorganic salts.
â— Incompatible With: Sulfur, phosphorus, finely powdered metals, strong acids, organic
matter, reducing agents.
22
ğŸš¨ Safety Notes
â— First Aid:
â—‹ Skin: Wash thoroughly with soap and water. Remove contaminated clothing.
â—‹ Eye: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes, seek immediate medical
attention.
â—‹ Inhalation: Move to fresh air, provide oxygen if necessary, seek medical
attention.
