â— Decomposition Products: Chlorine oxides, barium oxides, oxygen gas.
â— Disposal: Treat as highly hazardous waste. Must not be released into the environment.
Dispose of via licensed hazardous waste contractor.
âš ï¸ Note: Unlike KClOâ‚„ and KMnOâ‚„, barium chlorate combines high oxidizing power with
extreme toxicity due to soluble barium. Itâ€™s one of the most hazardous chlorates and rarely
