First Aid Quick Reference
Hazard Type First Aid Lab Notes
Skin Contact
(Acid/Base/Corrosive)
Flush with water for 15 min.
Remove contaminated clothing.
Seek medical aid.
Do not neutralize skin (heat
reaction).
Eye Contact Rinse eyes 15 min at eyewash
station, hold eyelids open. Get
medical help immediately.
Even mild chemicals â†’
always seek doctor
follow-up.
Inhalation (Dust, Gas,
Vapor)
Move to fresh air. Loosen
clothing. If breathing is difficult
â†’ oxygen. Call an emergency.
Use a fume hood to prevent
this. Never re-enter a
confined area.
Ingestion Do not induce vomiting. Rinse
mouth. Get medical aid
immediately.
Bring SDS to the ER. Some
chemicals worsen if vomited
(corrosives, oxidizers).
Burns (Thermal/Fire) Cool with running water. Cover
loosely with sterile gauze. Do
not apply oils/creams.
For Mg/metal fires â†’ never
water, use Class D
extinguishers.
Cuts / Lacerations Wash gently, control bleeding,
and apply sterile dressing. Seek
medical care.
Ensure tetanus shots are up
to date.
Chemical Spill on Body Safety shower immediately.
Remove clothing. Flush with
water for at least 15 min.
Have a buddy assist â€”
modesty < safety.
Fire / Explosion
Accident
Stop, drop, roll if on fire. Use a
fire blanket if nearby. Activate
alarm.
Always know extinguisher
locations.
